{
  "message": "chore(fuzz): seed fuzz_xdr corpus + gitignore auto-generated entries\n\nAdd 6 hand-crafted seed corpus entries for fuzz_xdr covering the\nshapes that took the longest for the libfuzzer mutation engine to\ndiscover during the bd-bhqcn campaign:\n\n- seed_minimal_decode (14B) \u2014 single Bool op against tiny stream\n- seed_xdr_int_roundtrip (18B) \u2014 Int(42) round-trip\n- seed_string_decode_short (21B) \u2014 StringDecode with bounded maxsize\n- seed_array_int_decode_zero_count (22B) \u2014 ArrayIntDecode (now\n  rejected by bd-bhqcn elsize=0 / overflow checks)\n- seed_oversized_length_lie (26B) \u2014 WrapstringDecode against a\n  4-byte length lie that decodes as ~4 GiB (caught by the\n  bd-bhqcn xdrmem_remaining_bytes guard)\n- seed_empty (1B) \u2014 boundary\n\nAlso add a corpus/*/[0-9a-f]* gitignore rule so future\n`git add corpus/` after a fuzz run doesn't commit thousands of\ncrypto-hash-named auto-generated entries \u2014 only hand-crafted\nseed_* files are tracked, matching the convention used by\nfuzz_inet, fuzz_ctype, and friends.",
  "files": [
    {
      "sha": "f8edfb32bd8b1406c0909ccf31b4822b0cae3338",
      "filename": "crates/frankenlibc-fuzz/.gitignore",
      "status": "modified",
      "additions": 6,
      "deletions": 0,
      "changes": 6,
      "blob_url": "https://github.com/Dicklesworthstone/frankenlibc/blob/15416cad242e4b632d139ff26c4f5efab27b72c5/crates%2Ffrankenlibc-fuzz%2F.gitignore",
      "raw_url": "https://github.com/Dicklesworthstone/frankenlibc/raw/15416cad242e4b632d139ff26c4f5efab27b72c5/crates%2Ffrankenlibc-fuzz%2F.gitignore",
      "contents_url": "https://api.github.com/repos/Dicklesworthstone/frankenlibc/contents/crates%2Ffrankenlibc-fuzz%2F.gitignore?ref=15416cad242e4b632d139ff26c4f5efab27b72c5",
      "patch": "@@ -1,3 +1,9 @@\n target\n Cargo.lock\n artifacts/\n+\n+# Auto-generated coverage entries from libfuzzer runs are not committed \u2014\n+# only hand-crafted `seed_*` entries are. Without this exclusion, a\n+# `git add corpus/` after a fuzz session would commit thousands of\n+# crypto-hash-named files.\n+corpus/*/[0-9a-f]*"
